---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy & Cookies" description="How R.E.A.CH (Reaching East Africa's CHildren) handles your information and uses cookies on this website.">
  <PageHeader eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy & Cookies" lead="How we handle your information and use cookies on this website." />

  <article class="container-reach py-16">
    <div class="prose-reach max-w-3xl">
      <p class="rounded-xl border border-sand-200 bg-sand-100/60 p-4 text-sm text-ink-600">
        This is a plain-English summary of how this website handles information. Trustees should
        review and adapt it to reflect the charity’s full data-handling practices before relying on it.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        R.E.A.CH (Reaching East Africa’s CHildren) is a UK registered charity (number {site.charityNumber}).
        For any questions about this policy or your information, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>, or by post at {site.address.name},
        {site.address.lines.join(', ')}.
      </p>

      <h2>The information we collect</h2>
      <p>
        This is a simple, static website. We do not run user accounts, and we do not sell or share
        your information for advertising. The main way we collect personal information is when you
        choose to contact us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form.</strong> If you send a message, we collect the name, email address and
          message you provide, so we can reply. These are delivered to our charity inbox and are not
          used for marketing.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email, phone and WhatsApp.</strong> If you contact us directly, we keep your message
          and details only for as long as needed to help you.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We keep cookies to a minimum. The site works without advertising or cross-site tracking
        cookies. The consent banner records your choice (accept or decline) in your browser’s local
        storage so we don’t ask again. If we later add website analytics to understand how the site is
        used, it will only run if you have accepted.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our contact form uses <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> to protect against spam. Turnstile
        is privacy-friendly and does not use cookies to track you across websites or serve advertising.
      </p>

      <h2>The services we rely on</h2>
      <p>
        To run the website securely we use a small number of reputable providers, who process limited
        technical data (such as your IP address) to deliver and protect the site:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> — hosts the website files.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — DNS, security and spam protection (Turnstile).</li>
        <li><strong>Formspree</strong> — delivers contact-form messages to our inbox.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK data protection law you have the right to ask for a copy of the personal information
        we hold about you, to have it corrected, or to have it deleted. To make a request, email us at
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>. You also have the right to complain to the
        Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) at ico.org.uk.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will appear on this page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <a href="/contact-us" class="btn-primary">Contact us</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
